The Champ is a 1979 American drama sports film directed by Franco Zeffirelli and a remake of the 1931 Academy Award-winning film of the same name which was directed by King Vidor .
It stars Jon Voight , Faye Dunaway , and Ricky Schroder .
It is also the final film for actress Joan Blondell to be released during her lifetime .
Blondell , who died from leukemia on Christmas Day eight months later , also starred in two other films that were released after her death .